investigation.title: RNA seq of tumors derived from irradiated versus sham hosts transplanted with Trp53 null mammary tissue and fed either Control diet versus Caffeic Acid Phenethyl Ester (CAPE) diet.
investigation.description: Irradiated hosts gave rise to significantly more Trp53 null mammary cancers that grew more rapidly than those in sham-irradiated mice and exhibited an immunosuppressive tumor microenvironment. CAPE prevented the effect of host irradiation on tumor growth rate, immune signature and immunosuppression.

project.funding: This research was supported by NASA Specialized Center for Research in Radiation Health Effects, NNX09AM52G at New York University School of Medicine, and NIH R01CA190980 and R01CA19098005S1 awards at University of California, San Francisco (to M.H. Barcellos-Hoff) and K08 CA172722 (to C. Omene).

protocols: User submitted sequence analysis data transformation
